      • addNormal

        public void addNormal(Vector3f normalToAdd,
             java.util.Map<Vector3f,Vector3f> normalMap,
             boolean smooth,
             Vector3f... vertices)
        This method adds a normal to a normals' map. This map is used to merge normals of a vertor that should be rendered smooth.
        Parameters:
        normalToAdd - a normal to be added
        normalMap - merges normals of faces that will be rendered smooth; the key is the vertex and the value - its normal vector
        smooth - the variable that indicates wheather to merge normals (creating the smooth mesh) or not
        vertices - a list of vertices read from the blender file

      • appendVertexReference

        protected void appendVertexReference(int basicVertexIndex,
                         int resultIndex,
                         java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.util.List<java.lang.Integer>> vertexReferenceMap)
        This method fills the vertex reference map. The vertices are loaded once and referenced many times in the model. This map is created to tell where the basic vertices are referenced in the result vertex lists. The key of the map is the basic vertex index, and its key - the reference indices list.
        Parameters:
        basicVertexIndex - the index of the vertex from its basic table
        resultIndex - the index of the vertex in its result vertex list
        vertexReferenceMap - the reference map

      • getVerticesColors

        public java.util.List<byte[]> getVerticesColors(Structure meshStructure,
                                       BlenderContext blenderContext)
                                         throws BlenderFileException
        This method returns the vertices colors. Each vertex is stored in byte[4] array.
        Parameters:
        meshStructure - the structure containing the mesh data
        blenderContext - the blender context
        Returns:
        a list of vertices colors, each color belongs to a single vertex
        Throws:
        BlenderFileException - this exception is thrown when the blend file structure is somehow invalid or corrupted
